President Obama expresses profound sadness over the death of Kayla Jean Mueller. He offers his deepest condolences to her family and all those who loved her. Kayla dedicated her life to helping others, volunteering at a women's shelter and an HIV/AIDS clinic. She also worked with humanitarian organizations in India, Israel, and the Palestinian territories. In Turkey, she provided support to Syrian refugees. President Obama praises Kayla's compassion and dedication, stating that she represents the best of America and the essential decency of humanity. He vows that the United States will find and bring to justice the terrorists responsible for Kayla's captivity and death. President Obama concludes by saying that Kayla's legacy will inspire others to fight for what is just and decent, and that the future belongs to the force of human goodness that she represents.